This is the story of the Crown of Stars Guild.  I hope you all enjoy it.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :O --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/embarassed.gif ALT=":O"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Chyra<br>
<br>
______________________________________________________<br>
<br>
Before the days of the Sundering, our home lands were filled with strife, overcrowding and evil deeds.  Kinslayers and Soulless ones walked among us openly, their cruel laughter ringing through the hills at those who were weaker, had less and could never hope for anything more.  Those few of us who finally fed up with this struggling life, lifted our tiny voices to the gods, begging them for mercy, for pity, for compassion… for change.  Although we witnessed no signs, we persevered, adding new voices to our cry until at last our voices rose up to the Heavens with a thundering roar!  The gods would answer our prayers and give us salvation – but at a price.<br>
<br>
We did not care what price would be asked of us, we were overjoyed at finally having gotten the attention of our aloof gods.  Eagerly, those of us who wished to leave our home land, gathered up our belongings, leaving nothing behind for the Soulless ones to scavenge.  Among the Western Commonlands, we gathered to await the will of the gods.  With laughter, with singing, with hope in our hearts we formed great circles of dancing to praise the heavens.<br>
<br>
As the midnight hours grew longer, we saw a blue light, streaking across the night sky to grow larger as it approached us – a comet.  We gazed at it in awe, every one of us staring up and pointing as it grew impossibly large and always closer until it became too intense and we had to close our eyes or lose our sight forever.  With eyes closed, we heard the impact, a gigantic crashing such as we never heard before nor will hear again.  Then -  pure silence.<br>
<br>
We felt nothing.  We saw nothing.  We knew not if we sat, or stood, or lay.  We merely heard.  The sound of ultimate harmony, not in words but in feelings which washed over us to soothe and comfort our souls.  We listened as the gods spoke into our hearts.  The gods would take a chosen few to dwell upon a new world.  Families would be broken and loved ones left behind.  We would never be allowed to return to our original home lands in our physical bodies.  That was the price to be paid.  Each of us was allowed to make their decision in the silence of their soul where the gods read our secret desires.<br>
<br>
The few who were Chosen, were slowly lifted up into the air, spinning in a last dance, in an outpouring of love, of emotions so strong not even tears could express them.  They spun, each of them, and they spun in a larger circle, a dance of life and new hope.  And continued to rise, floating and spinning up into the Heavens, and as they grew smaller in sight, they began to glow, to shine with light until they were a circle of dancing stars in the sky – a Crown of Stars.<br>
<br>
Those left behind in the Sundering did not cry.  They would always be able to look up into the night sky and see the new constellation there – Saryrn – and know that once, the gods heard their prayers, hope was never to be lost.  One day in the future, others might be Chosen to join Saryrn, but until then, this symbol of hope would shine brightly for all to gaze upon and renew their faith and hope in the gods.<br>
